result.name: Sour & Spicy Noodle

reviews.text: Had spicy and sour soup with potato noodles with some cucumbers for HKD 54. Only little spicy (小辣) but it was spicy enough for me. It was delicious and I would go back to the place for the same dish. Staff neutral (nothing good nothing bad), great location, I would recommend to friends.
Spicy food and don't forget the points via their apps

Speedy, cheap and reliable Sichuan food. If this is what you're after you'd be hard pressed to find a better place. Don't expect great service or an especially 'clean and tidy' setting, do expect satisfying food made to your taste.

If you like spicy Asian food this is a good place for it. Like any popular place in Hong Kong there can be a bit of a wait during peak times. If it's your first time be warned, start with the mildest level. Medium and above are seriously spicy. Pricing is decent. Setting is casual. Only minus is the seating. Can be quite tight when it is full.
Good spicy noodles place, popular among young people. You always needed to wait but the waiting was never too long. Recently they gave out complimentary watermelons for the hot summer!

海鮮又夠新鮮, 我同家人都幫襯咗5,6次
金百利中心 不但是shopping的好去處， 中心樓上亦有不同食肆， 不同樓層更有不同的風味食肆， 任君選擇…… 韓式港式 西餐廳應有盡有
鐵板燒牛肉飯味道不錯，中間還有隻溫泉蛋，價格還可以，可以再試。
交通方更，幾層樓都係食店
還不錯，但會考慮在網拍買。
